rComments: I loved this course and how it was taught! You work hard for your grades but I do believe this course sets the bar for the other theatre courses the students of that program will be taking, making sure they know how hard to work and how to meet a prof's expectations.

This teacher is hilarious; gives good, clear lectures; and very well conveys the material in a fun, interactive way. The whole class is always engaged in discussion and everybody laughs along. The course is reading/project heavy, though, so watch out! She likes pop quizzes too, but if you do the work you'll be fine.  Beware: she takes attendance!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Hilarious']

rComments: She's a good prof in general. She gives us a lot of information in lectures and they're either boring as hell or slightly interesting. She makes quite a few jokes so she isn't bad at all. I wouldn't mind having her again... p.s. dont buy the book! the class textbook is barely used and when it is you can just go get a photocopy at the library!

She is the worst prof I've had. Syllabus doesn't make any sense at all and she's more there to give a show and to show how cool she is than to teach. Completely unhelpful or willing to help out outside of class.
Good Prof. You work hard but if you do, you get good grades.
